Well. he signed today. The consensus on this one stayed low until the end. A bit of post-mortem why (in my view):
- early on, the prevailing opinion was that after the health care debacle in the spring, no new attempts will be made this year;
- later, when the issue appeared in the tax bill, the view shifted that it won't survive in the final version owing to resistance by some Senate Rs;
- finally, when the Senate voted for it, there was skepticism that the law can be signed before end-2017 (including until yesterday, because of PAYGO provisions).
